 genus name, <em>Acidovorax</em>; N.L. masc. n. <em>Pseudacidovorax</em> the false <em>Acidovorax</em>).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Cells are Gram-negative, short rods that are motile by a polar flagellum.</s><s>Facultatively aerobic.</s><s>Growth occurs after 96 h incubation on TSA and nutrient agar at 30 °C.</s><s>Major fatty acids are C<sub>16 : 0</sub>, C<sub>18 : 1</sub><em>ω</em>7<em>c</em> and summed feature 3 (C<sub>16 : 1</sub><em>ω</em>7<em>c</em>/C<sub>15 : 0</sub> iso 2-OH).</s><s>The hydroxylated fatty acids C<sub>8 : 0</sub> 3-OH, C<sub>10 : 0</sub> 3-OH, C<sub>16 : 1</sub> 2-OH and C<sub>18 : 1</sub> 2-OH are also present.</s><s>The type and only species is <em>Pseudacidovorax intermedius</em>.</s></p></content></protolog>